<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>World-Class Smart Contract Developer Roadmap</title>
    <!-- External Dependencies -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500;600&family=Space+Mono:wght@400;700&family=Syne:wght@600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css">
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg-color: #060810;
            --sidebar-bg: #0c0f1a;
            --accent-cyan: #00d4ff;
            --accent-purple: #7c3aed;
            --accent-amber: #f59e0b;
            --accent-red: #ef4444;
            --accent-green: #10b981;
            --text-primary: #e2e8f0;
            --text-secondary: #94a3b8;
            --border-color: #1e293b;
            --card-bg: #111422;
            --sidebar-width: 280px;
            --font-heading: 'Syne', sans-serif;
            --font-code: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
            --font-number: 'Space Mono', monospace;
            --transition: all 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
        }

        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            scroll-behavior: smooth;
        }

        body {
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            color: var(--text-primary);
            font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            overflow-x: hidden;
        }

        /* --- Sidebar --- */
        .sidebar {
            position: fixed;
            left: 0;
            top: 0;
            width: var(--sidebar-width);
            height: 100vh;
            background: var(--sidebar-bg);
            border-right: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding: 1.5rem;
            overflow-y: auto;
            z-index: 1000;
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }

        .sidebar-logo {
            font-family: var(--font-heading);
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
        }

        .nav-group {
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        .nav-group-title {
            font-family: var(--font-heading);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
            color: var(--accent-purple);
            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
            padding-left: 0.5rem;
        }

        .nav-item {
            display: block;
            padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            border-radius: 6px;
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
            margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
        }

        .nav-item:hover {
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
            background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.05);
        }

        .nav-item.active {
            color: var(--text-primary);
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.2) 0%, rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1) 100%);
            border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-cyan);
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        /* --- Main Content --- */
        .main-content {
            margin-left: var(--sidebar-width);
            padding: 0;
        }

        section {
            padding: 6rem 4rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        /* --- Hero Section --- */
        .hero {
            height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            background: radial-gradient(circle at 50% 50%, rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.1) 0%, transparent 50%);
        }

        .hero h1 {
            font-family: var(--font-heading);
            font-size: 4rem;
            line-height: 1.1;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--text-primary) 0%, var(--text-secondary) 100%);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        }

        .hero p {
            font-size: 1.25rem;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            max-width: 700px;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
        }

        .stats-row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 2.5rem;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }

        .stat-item {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }

        .stat-value {
            font-family: var(--font-number);
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .stat-label {
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        }

        /* --- Stage Components --- */
        h2 {
            font-family: var(--font-heading);
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: var(--text-primary);
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 1rem;
        }

        h2::before {
            content: '';
            width: 4px;
            height: 2.5rem;
            background: var(--accent-purple);
            display: inline-block;
        }

        h3 {
            font-family: var(--font-heading);
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin: 2.5rem 0 1.25rem;
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            font-size: 1.05rem;
        }

        strong {
            color: var(--text-primary);
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .code-block-container {
            position: relative;
            margin: 1.5rem 0;
        }

        .code-block {
            background: #0d1117;
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            font-family: var(--font-code);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: #d1d5db;
            overflow-x: auto;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        .copy-btn {
            position: absolute;
            top: 0.75rem;
            right: 0.75rem;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            padding: 0.4rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            transition: var(--transition);
        }

        .copy-btn:hover {
            background: var(--accent-cyan);
            color: white;
            border-color: var(--accent-cyan);
        }

        .callout {
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 2rem 0;
            display: flex;
            gap: 1rem;
            align-items: flex-start;
            border: 1px solid;
        }

        .callout-iron {
            background: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.05);
            border-color: #94a3b8;
            color: #94a3b8;
        }

        .callout-danger {
            background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.05);
            border-color: var(--accent-red);
            color: var(--accent-red);
        }

        .callout-title {
            font-weight: 800;
            margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
            display: block;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
        }

        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 2rem 0;
            background: var(--card-bg);
            border-radius: 8px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        th, td {
            padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
            text-align: left;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }

        th {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
            font-family: var(--font-heading);
            color: var(--accent-cyan);
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        }

        .video-container {
            position: relative;
            margin: 2.5rem 0;
            border-radius: 12px;
            overflow: hidden;
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            aspect-ratio: 16/9;
        }

        /* --- Scroll to Top --- */
        #scrollTop {
            position: fixed;
            bottom: 2rem;
            right: 1.5rem;
            background: var(--accent-purple);
            color: white;
            width: 3rem;
            height: 3rem;
            border-radius: 50%;
            display: none;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            cursor: pointer;
            z-index: 1001;
            border: none;
            transition: var(--transition);
        }

        /* --- Mobile --- */
        .mobile-menu-btn {
            display: none;
            position: fixed;
            top: 1rem;
            left: 1rem;
            z-index: 1002;
            background: var(--sidebar-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            color: var(--text-primary);
            padding: 0.75rem;
            border-radius: 8px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        @media (max-width: 1024px) {
            .sidebar { transform: translateX(-100%); width: 100%; max-width: 320px; }
            .sidebar.open { transform: translateX(0); }
            .main-content { margin-left: 0; }
            .mobile-menu-btn { display: block; }
            section { padding: 4rem 1.5rem; }
            .hero h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <button class="mobile-menu-btn" id="mobileMenuBtn"><i class="fas fa-bars"></i></button>

    <aside class="sidebar" id="sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar-logo">
            <i class="fas fa-cube"></i>
            <span>CHAINCODECAMP</span>
        </div>

        <div class="nav-group">
            <div class="nav-group-title">Foundation</div>
            <a href="#prerequisites" class="nav-item">Prerequisites</a>
            <a href="#evm-internals" class="nav-item">EVM Internals</a>
            <a href="#solidity-yul" class="nav-item">Solidity + Yul</a>
            <a href="#languages" class="nav-item">Languages</a>
            <a href="#tools" class="nav-item">Tools</a>
        </div>

        <div class="nav-group">
            <div class="nav-group-title">Core Mastery</div>
            <a href="#security" class="nav-item">Security & Auditing</a>
            <a href="#gas" class="nav-item">Gas Optimization</a>
            <a href="#tokens" class="nav-item">Token Standards</a>
            <a href="#proxies" class="nav-item">Proxies & Upgrades</a>
            <a href="#defi" class="nav-item">DeFi Architecture</a>
        </div>

        <div class="nav-group">
            <div class="nav-group-title">Advanced</div>
            <a href="#mev" class="nav-item">MEV Infrastructure</a>
            <a href="#aa" class="nav-item">Account Abstraction</a>
            <a href="#zk" class="nav-item">Zero-Knowledge</a>
            <a href="#l2" class="nav-item">Layer 2 & Bridges</a>
            <a href="#tokenomics" class="nav-item">Tokenomics Deep Dive</a>
        </div>

        <div class="nav-group">
            <div class="nav-group-title">Build & Grow</div>
            <a href="#projects" class="nav-item">8 Projects</a>
            <a href="#recognition" class="nav-item">Recognition</a>
            <a href="#routine" class="nav-item">Daily Routine</a>
            <a href="#plan" class="nav-item">6-Month Plan</a>
            <a href="#elite" class="nav-item">Elite Knowledge</a>
        </div>
    </aside>

    <main class="main-content">
        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <section id="hero" class="hero">
            <h1>World-Class Smart Contract Developer Roadmap</h1>
            <p>From zero to protocol architect. Every exploit explained. Every concept proven. Security is the entire job.</p>
            <div class="stats-row">
                <div class="stat-item">
                    <span class="stat-value">17</span>
                    <span class="stat-label">Stages</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-item">
                    <span class="stat-value">200+</span>
                    <span class="stat-label">Topics</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-item">
                    <span class="stat-value">8</span>
                    <span class="stat-label">Projects</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-item">
                    <span class="stat-value">6 Mo</span>
                    <span class="stat-label">Duration</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-item">
                    <span class="stat-value">$2B+</span>
                    <span class="stat-label">Exploits Studied</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Stage 00: Prerequisites -->
        <section id="prerequisites">
            <h2>Stage 00: Prerequisites</h2>
            <p>Before writing a single line of Solidity, you must understand the environment your code lives in. A blockchain is not a cloud server; it is a <strong>globally replicated append-only database</strong>.</p>
            
            <h3>Public-Key Cryptography</h3>
            <p>The foundation of identity on Ethereum. Your account is a pair of cryptographic keys:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Private Key:</strong> A random 256-bit number. This is your soul; if lost, your funds are gone.</li>
                <li><strong>Public Key:</strong> Derived from the private key using <strong>ECDSA</strong> (Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm).</li>
                <li><strong>Address:</strong> Derived by taking the <code>keccak256</code> hash of the public key and keeping the <strong>last 20 bytes</strong>.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>What is a Transaction?</h3>
            <p>A transaction is a signed message that triggers a state change. It contains:</p>
            <div class="code-block-container">
                <button class="copy-btn"><i class="far fa-copy"></i></button>
                <div class="code-block">
{
    "nonce": 1, // Prevent replay attacks
    "gasPrice": 20000000000, // Price per gas unit
    "gasLimit": 21000, // Max gas for this tx
    "to": "0x...", // Destination address
    "value": 1000000000000000000, // Amount in Wei (1 ETH)
    "data": "0x", // Input for contract calls
    "v, r, s": "..." // ECDSA signature components
}</div>
            </div>

            <div class="callout callout-iron">
                <i class="fas fa-gavel"></i>
                <div>
                    <span class="callout-title">The Iron Rule</span>
                    Code is law. Bugs ARE the law. In a decentralized world, there is no "undo" button. If your contract has a vulnerability, it is a feature of the protocol until fixed.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="video-container">
                <iframe width="100%" height="100%" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/SSo_EIwHSd4" title="But how does Bitcoin actually work?" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Stage 01: EVM Internals -->
        <section id="evm-internals">
            <h2>Stage 01: EVM Internals</h2>
            <p>The Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) is a <strong>stack-based state machine</strong>. Think of a stack of plates: you can only add (PUSH) or remove (POP) from the top.</p>
            
            <h3>The 4 Data Locations</h3>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Location</th>
                        <th>Gas Cost</th>
                        <th>Nature</th>
                        <th>Security Significance</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Stack</strong></td>
                        <td>3-5 gas</td>
                        <td>Volatile</td>
                        <td>1024 slots. Source of "Stack too deep" errors.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Memory</strong></td>
                        <td>Quadratic</td>
                        <td>Volatile</td>
                        <td>Expansion cost: <code>3n + n²/512</code>. Layout 0x00-0x80 scratch.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Storage</strong></td>
                        <td>20k / 2.1k</td>
                        <td>Permanent</td>
                        <td>Cold SLOAD (2100) and SSTORE (20000) drive all costs.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Calldata</strong></td>
                        <td>4-16 gas</td>
                        <td>Read-only</td>
                        <td>Cheap input data. 4 per zero byte, 16 per non-zero.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <div class="callout callout-danger">
                <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
                <div>
                    <span class="callout-title">DELEGATECALL Danger</span>
                    DELEGATECALL runs external code in YOUR storage context. A malicious implementation can overwrite ANY storage slot including the owner/admin slots.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="video-container">
                <iframe width="100%" height="100%" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/RxL_1AfV7N4" title="EVM Deep Dive" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Stage 02: Solidity + Yul -->
        <section id="solidity-yul">
            <h2>Stage 02: Solidity + Yul</h2>
            <p>Solidity is the high-level language, but Yul is the assembly language that gives you surgical control over the EVM.</p>
            
            <h3>Storage Layout Packing</h3>
            <p>Packing variables into a single 32-byte slot saves 20,000 gas per slot avoided.</p>
            <div class="code-block-container">
                <button class="copy-btn"><i class="far fa-copy"></i></button>
                <div class="code-block">
// BAD: 3 slots (60,000 gas to initialize)
uint256 a; // Slot 0
uint128 b; // Slot 1
uint256 c; // Slot 2

// GOOD: 2 slots (40,000 gas to initialize)
uint256 a; // Slot 0
uint128 b; // Slot 1 (packs with d)
uint128 d; // Slot 1</div>
            </div>

            <h3>Slot Derivation Rules</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Mappings:</strong> <code>keccak256(abi.encode(key, p))</code> where <code>p</code> is the slot of the mapping.</li>
                <li><strong>Arrays:</strong> Length at slot <code>p</code>, elements start at <code>keccak256(p)</code>.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="callout callout-iron">
                <i class="fas fa-microchip"></i>
                <div>
                    <span class="callout-title">Optimization Rule</span>
                    Reading WETH from an immutable variable costs 3 gas. Reading it from storage costs 2,100 gas. At 10,000 calls/day, this saves 20.9M gas daily.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="video-container">
                <iframe width="100%" height="100%" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/umepbfKp5rI" title="Foundry Full Course" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Stage 03: Languages to Master -->
        <section id="languages">
            <h2>Stage 03: Languages to Master</h2>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Language</th>
                        <th>Depth</th>
                        <th>Role</th>
                        <th>Resource</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Solidity</td>
                        <td>Expert</td>
                        <td>Primary smart contract language.</td>
                        <td><a href="https://docs.soliditylang.org/" target="_blank">Docs</a></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Yul</td>
                        <td>Proficient</td>
                        <td>Gas optimization and low-level control.</td>
                        <td><a href="https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/latest/yul.html" target="_blank">Yul Docs</a></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>TypeScript</td>
                        <td>Expert</td>
                        <td>Testing (Ethers/Viem) and Frontend.</td>
                        <td><a href="https://viem.sh/" target="_blank">Viem Docs</a></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Rust</td>
                        <td>Proficient</td>
                        <td>Foundry tooling and MEV bots.</td>
                        <td><a href="https://www.rust-lang.org/" target="_blank">Rust Lang</a></td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </section>

        <!-- Stage 04: Professional Toolchain -->
        <section id="tools">
            <h2>Stage 04: Professional Toolchain</h2>
            <h3>Foundry</h3>
            <p>The industry standard for smart contract development.</p>
            <div class="code-block-container">
                <button class="copy-btn"><i class="far fa-copy"></i></button>
                <div class="code-block">
curl -L https://foundry.paradigm.xyz | bash
foundryup

forge build   // Compile
forge test    // Run tests
forge test -vvvv // Full debug trace
cast storage 0x... 0 // Read slot 0</div>
            </div>
            
            <h3>Security Tools</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Slither:</strong> Static analysis for common vulnerabilities.</li>
                <li><strong>Echidna:</strong> Fuzzing tool for property-based testing.</li>
                <li><strong>Halmos:</strong> Formal verification for EVM bytecode.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Stage 05: Security & Auditing -->
        <section id="security">
            <h2>Stage 05: Security & Auditing</h2>
            <p>Security is not a stage; it is the entire job. You must learn to think like an attacker.</p>
            
            <h3>Vulnerability: Reentrancy</h3>
            <p>The exploit that birthed Ethereum Classic. The DAO Hack ($60M, 2016).</p>
            <div class="code-block-container">
                <button class="copy-btn"><i class="far fa-copy"></i></button>
                <div class="code-block">
// VULNERABLE
function withdraw() public {
    uint balance = balances[msg.sender];
    (bool success, ) = msg.sender.call{value: balance}("");
    balances[msg.sender] = 0; // State updated AFTER call
}

// FIXED (Checks-Effects-Interactions)
function withdraw() public {
    uint balance = balances[msg.sender];
    balances[msg.sender] = 0; // State updated BEFORE call
    (bool success, ) = msg.sender.call{value: balance}("");
    require(success);
}</div>
            </div>

            <h3>Rekt Hall of Fame</h3>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Protocol</th>
                        <th>Loss</th>
                        <th>Type</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Ronin</td>
                        <td>$625M</td>
                        <td>Key Compromise</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Nomad</td>
                        <td>$190M</td>
                        <td>Logic Error</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Beanstalk</td>
                        <td>$182M</td>
                        <td>Governance/Flash Loan</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <div class="video-container">
                <iframe width="100%" height="100%" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/DRZogmD647U" title="Smart Contract Security" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Stage 06: Gas Optimization -->
        <section id="gas">
            <h2>Stage 06: Gas Optimization</h2>
            <div class="code-block-container">
                <div class="code-block">
// 1. Cache storage reads (ROI: Massive)
uint256 cached = storageVar; // 2100 gas
// use cached 3 times (3 gas each) instead of storageVar (2100 gas each)
// Saves 4200 gas per call.</div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Stage 07: Token Standards -->
        <section id="tokens">
            <h2>Stage 07: Token Standards</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>ERC-20:</strong> Fungible tokens (USDT, USDC). Watch for non-standard returns.</li>
                <li><strong>ERC-721:</strong> NFTs. safeTransferFrom reentrancy risk.</li>
                <li><strong>ERC-4626:</strong> Tokenized Vaults. Rounding errors = exploit vector.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Stage 08: Proxies & Upgrades -->
        <section id="proxies">
            <h2>Stage 08: Proxies & Upgrades</h2>
            <p>Proxies allow updating code while keeping state. Storage layout gaps are critical.</p>
            <div class="callout callout-danger">
                <span class="callout-title">Storage Gap Warning</span>
                Adding a variable in a parent contract without gaps shifts ALL child variables. State is permanently corrupted.
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Stage 09: DeFi Architecture -->
        <section id="defi">
            <h2>Stage 09: DeFi Architecture</h2>
